                            <comment id="13691139" author="sbtourist" created="Sat, 22 Jun 2013 13:17:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I run into this one too: it is caused by ReadResponse not correctly computing the serialized payload size in case of digest reads; this is not a problem for 1.2, which doesn&apos;t really use the payload size to read from the stream, but actually is for 1.1 which uses it for deserializing the ReadResponse coming from a 1.2 node.&lt;br/&gt;
To reproduce, just run a replicated cluster with mixed 1.1 and 1.2 nodes, increment the read repair chance to 1, insert some data and query from a 1.1 node (as the problem is the response back from 1.2 nodes).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13691158" author="iamaleksey" created="Sat, 22 Jun 2013 13:58:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks. Committed in 57eb87b57cc7c69d99238ced08e50cc23b0127ba.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
